      "date": "2014-01-27 22:33:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(5 comments)\n\nI think this would really benefit from the other cache improvements that Tao wrote for the original replacement that was using ->read and ->write.\n\nFor the initial upstream submission it might just be easier to use \"lctl set_param jobid_var=direct:{jobid}\" and avoid the whole upcall mechanism.  Less to review, and less for the upstream to be unhappy about in the short term.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
